# Concepts

## 1. From audiences to networks
Creators are typically treated as isolated entities.  
This explores how they can exist as connected nodes instead.

## 2. Growth as a shared system
Instead of competing for attention, creators can participate in systems where visibility is distributed through collaboration.

## 3. Discovery through proximity
What you see is not based on algorithms alone, but on your position within a network of creators.

## 4. Circles over feeds
Replacing linear content consumption with structured, interconnected creator groups.

## 5. Identity as a network node
A creator is not just a profile, but a position within a living system.
